SUBJECT_PROJECT.MarketTrendsReconciliationComment: Effective Date: Wednesday, September 3, 2014 The inventory analysis predominantly indicates a stable market. The median comparable sale price indicates a stable market. The median comparable list price reflects a declining market, but this figure is based on only one listing for the current period. Most other indicators point to a stable or improving market. This information, together with the appraiser's experience and knowledge, indicates a stable market.

PROJECT._CommonElementsDescription: The project features a club/exercise room, a swimming pool and a spa. Several fountains and ponds are located throughout the project in the common areas.
PROJECT._ConditionAndQualityDescription: The subject's project has been well maintained and is constructed of good quality materials. The exterior consists of stone, stucco and trim and has good market appeal.

NEIGHBORHOOD._Description: Homes in the neighborhood vary in age, style, construction quality, and overall appeal, but are compatible with one another. Schools, houses of worship and city parks are available nearby. Major shopping and employment opportunities are available two miles to the west in Riverdale City. There is a good road system in the area and access is convenient.

LISTING_HISTORY.ListedWithinPreviousYearDescription: According to MLS# 1251200, the subject was listed on 08/13/2014 for $95,000. It went under contract on 08/26/2014.

PROPERTY_ANALYSIS._Comment: The improvements have been well maintained and feature only minimal physical depreciation due to normal wear and tear. No deferred maintenance was noted. The interior decor is neutral in color and and has average to good appeal. No significant updates have taken place recently, but the structure itself, together with the improvements, has been well maintained.
No adverse site conditions or external factors were noted in the area that would adversely affect the subject property's value.
The subject features thermopane windows and a gas fireplace.

SALES_CONTRACT._ReviewComment: The purchase contract is the typical six page report and contains two addenda. The contract is straight forward with no unusual terms or conditions.

SALES_COMPARISON._Comment: The comparable sales bracket the subject in gross living area (GLA), sales price and adjusted sales price. Specific adjustments are made as follows: Based on interior MLS photos, Comp 1 is dated and is inferior in condition. An upward adjustment is made accordingly. It brackets on the low-end of GLA. Comp 1 has an extra half bath and is slightly larger in GLA. It is otherwise similar to the subject. Comp 3 is similar in most aspects to the subject. Comp 4 is an REO property and is a two-story structure. Additionally, it is much larger in GLA. Less weight is therefore placed on this comp. Comp 5 is currently under contract and a downward adjustment is made for the sale to list price ratio. It too is larger in GLA. The final value is based on Comps 1 and 2 as they have the least amount of adjustments and are the most similar to the subject. However, the final value is rounded down to the sales price of $90,000.
SALES_COMPARISON._CurrentSalesAgreementAnalysisComment: The subject has not been sold or listed during the prior three years. With the exception of Comps 1 and 3, the comparable sales have not transferred title during the prior year other than what is indicated in the sales comparison grid. Comp 1 transferred title on 12/23/2013. Comp 3 transferred title on 9/26/2013 as part of a trustee's deed and more recently on 10/15/2013. However, because Utah is a non-disclosure state, the sales prices of these transactions are not available.

_RECONCILIATION._SummaryComment: The value is based on the sales approach. The cost approach is not applicable on condos like the subject. The income approach was not used due to lack of data. The scope of the appraisal includes the appraisal process except as noted. The intended client is shown herein but it is understood that others may read the report. The purpose of the appraisal is to estimate the value for a mortgage transaction.
